# Plan: Add Pagination to GET /users

## Context

The `GET /users` endpoint currently returns the full `users` array as a flat JSON array. The tests in `tests/routes.test.ts` already expect a paginated response with a `data` array and a `pagination` metadata object. This plan adds `page` and `limit` query parameter support, making the endpoint return a subset of users along with pagination metadata.

---

## Critical File

**Only one file needs to change:**
- `src/routes.ts`

---

## Implementation

### Replace the `GET /users` handler in `src/routes.ts` (lines 7–9)

**Current code:**
```typescript
// GET /users - returns all users
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json(users);
});
```

**New code:**
```typescript
// GET /users - returns paginated users
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1;
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10;

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const startIndex = (page - 1) * limit;

  const data = users.slice(startIndex, startIndex + limit);

  res.json({
    data,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages },
  });
});
```

### Logic notes
| Concern | Handling |
|---|---|
| Default `page` | `1` (via `|| 1` fallback) |
| Default `limit` | `10` (via `|| 10` fallback) |
| Out-of-range page | `Array.slice()` returns `[]` when `startIndex >= total` — no special case needed |
| `totalPages` | `Math.ceil(15 / 10) = 2`; `Math.ceil(15 / 5) = 3` — matches test expectations |

No other files need changes. `GET /users/:id`, `src/app.ts`, `src/data.ts`, and `src/types.ts` are all unaffected.

---

## Verification

Run the existing test suite:
```bash
npm test
```

